					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7304162#post-3949601</guid>
				<title>Re: Of Mice and Twine</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7304162/scp-4016#post-3949601</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 01 Sep 2018 20:09:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zyn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1404533</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Okay, so this was a really fun project that actually didn't take too long to finalize because we hit the ground running with the ideas. <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/alces-alces" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4057128&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1535836126" alt="Alces_alces" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4057128)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/alces-alces" >Alces_alces</a></span> (whose carabiner SCP I really like) originally reached out to me asking for feedback on the draft, and I reviewed it while pretty tired and crabby (sorry, Alces) but then later came back to read it again and found that I really liked the concept and the overall tone. We talked about a few polish-up tweaks and story elements, edits were made, we got feedback from lots of people (thank you all so, so much!) and now here we are.</p> <p>When reading the original draft, I was getting vibes of mythological golems created out of simple materials and given life (using a piece of paper or through a word of power written on its forehead) to serve masters. And it got me thinking, what happens to a golem whose master is gone? What happens to a golem who doesn't want to perform its former tasks? What does a golem do with its freedom?</p> <p>Also I had the mental image of samurai, who would be bloodthirsty on the battlefield, but engage in artistic pursuits like flower arrangement to purify the heart and mind.</p> <p>To those reading, thanks for your time, and I hope you enjoy the piece!</p> <p>ETA: also, Alces made the twine man in the picture! How cool is that?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7304162#post-3949588</guid>
				<title>Of Mice and Twine</title>
